class Sandpile():
    
    def stabilize(self):
        it = 0
        while (self.vMax() >= 4):
            a = 0
            b = 0
            for i in self.mat:
                for j in i:
                    if(self.topple(a,b)==True):
                        self.show()
                        it += 1
                    b += 1
                b = 0
                a += 1
        show("Stable state reached after "+str(it)+" topplings")
        self.vmax = self.vMax()
    
    def topple(self,i,j):
        if(i < 0 or i >= self.mat.nrows() or j < 0 or j>= self.mat.ncols()):
            return False
        
        if(self.mat[i][j]>= 4):
            if(i-1 >= 0):
                self.mat[i-1,j] += 1
            if(j-1 >= 0):
                self.mat[i,j-1] += 1
            if(i+1 < self.mat.nrows()):
                self.mat[i+1,j] += 1
            if(j+1 < self.mat.ncols()):
                self.mat[i,j+1] += 1
            self.mat[i,j] -= 4
            return True
        return False
    
    def vMax(self):
        vmax=0
        for i in self.mat:
            for j in i:
                if(j>vmax):
                    vmax = j
        return vmax
    
    def show(self):
        G = Graphics()
        a = 0
        for i in self.mat:
            b = -1
            for j in i:
                G += polygon([[a,b],[a+1,b],[a+1,b+1],[a,b+1]],rgbcolor=(1-(j/self.vmax),1-(j/self.vmax),0))
                b-=1
            a+=1
        show(G, axes = false)
    def __init__(self, mat):
        
        self.mat = matrix(mat)
        self.vmax = self.vMax()
​
    def __repr__(self):
    
        return self.mat.__repr__()
